alvarion802dot11.name: alvarion802dot11
alvarion802dot11.contactinfo: Alvarion Ltd. Postal: 21a HaBarzel St. P.O. Box 13139 Tel-Aviv 69710 Israel Phone: +972 3 645 6262
alvarion802dot11.description: The MIB module for IEEE 802.11 entities.

coDot11AccessPointConfigTable.name: coDot11AccessPointConfigTable
coDot11AccessPointConfigTable.description: WLAN profile configuration attributes. In tablular form to allow for multiple instances on an agent. Not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11AccessPointConfigEntry.name: coDot11AccessPointConfigEntry
coDot11AccessPointConfigEntry.description: An entry in the coDot11AccessPointConfigTable. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex. coVirtualWlanProfileIndex - Uniquely access a profile for this particular 802.11 interface.

coDot11RelayBetweenStation.name: coDot11RelayBetweenStation
coDot11RelayBetweenStation.description: Specifies if wireless client stations can exchange data with one another.

coDot11BeaconPeriod.name: coDot11BeaconPeriod
coDot11BeaconPeriod.description: Indicates the number of TUs that a station uses for scheduling Beacon transmissions. This value is transmitted in Beacon and Probe Response frames.

coDot11DTIMPeriod.name: coDot11DTIMPeriod
coDot11DTIMPeriod.description: Specifies the number of beacon intervals that elapses between transmission of Beacons frames containing a TIM element whose DTIM Count field is 0. This value is transmitted in the DTIM Period field of Beacon frames. Client stations use the DTIM to wake up from low-power mode to receive multicast traffic.

coDot11PrivacyOptionImplemented.name: coDot11PrivacyOptionImplemented
coDot11PrivacyOptionImplemented.description: Indicates if the IEEE 802.11 WEP option is enabled.

coDot11RSNAOptionImplemented.name: coDot11RSNAOptionImplemented
coDot11RSNAOptionImplemented.description: Indicates if the profile is RSNA-capable.

coDot11NumberOfUsers.name: coDot11NumberOfUsers
coDot11NumberOfUsers.description: Indicates the number of users connected via this profile.

coDot11AddToAssociationNotification.name: coDot11AddToAssociationNotification
coDot11AddToAssociationNotification.description: Specifies if an association trap notification is sent each time a user connects to this profile.

coDot11PhyTxPowerAdminLevel.name: coDot11PhyTxPowerAdminLevel
coDot11PhyTxPowerAdminLevel.description: Specifies the transmission power of the radio. On Intersil hardware, only a few specific values are allowed. { 13, 17, 23 } for North America, { 13, 17, 20 } for Europe and the rest of the world.

coDot11CurrentSNRLevel.name: coDot11CurrentSNRLevel
coDot11CurrentSNRLevel.description: Average SNR level for all the connected client stations.

coDot11BSSID.name: coDot11BSSID
coDot11BSSID.description: MAC Address assigned to this device.

coDot11AdminMinimumDataRate.name: coDot11AdminMinimumDataRate
coDot11AdminMinimumDataRate.description: Specifies the minimum transmission rate that clients stations must meet in order to connect with this profile. Client stations that are below this setting will not be able to connect. The value of this object must always be less or equal than the value of coDot11MaximumDataRate. Allowed values will change according to the state of the radio's wireless mode (coDot11CurrentOperPHYType). ieee802dot11b: Lowest, 1, 2, 5.5, and 11 Meg ieee802dot11a: Lowest, 6, 9, 12, 18, 24, 36, 48, and 54 Meg ieee802dot11g: Lowest, 6, 9, 12, 18, 24, 36, 48, and 54 Meg 11bAndg: All rates permitted.

coDot11AdminMaximumDataRate.name: coDot11AdminMaximumDataRate
coDot11AdminMaximumDataRate.description: Specifies the maximum transmission rate that clients stations must respect to connect with this profile. Clients stations that attempt to associate at a higher data rate will be refused. The value of this object must always be greater than the value of coDot11MinimumDataRate. Allowed values will change according to the state of the radio's wireless mode (coDot11CurrentOperPHYType). ieee802dot11b: 1, 2, 5.5, 11Meg and highest ieee802dot11a: 6, 9, 12, 18, 24, 36, 48, 54 Meg, and highest ieee802dot11g: 6, 9, 12, 18, 24, 36, 48, 54 Meg, and highest 11bAndg: All rates permitted.

coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsTable.name: coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsTable
coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsTable.description: This (conceptual) table of attributes is a set of all the authentication algorithms supported by the stations. The following are the default values and the associated algorithm: Value = 1: Open System Value = 2: Shared Key

coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEntry.name: coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEntry
coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the Authentication Algorithms Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex. coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex - Uniquely identify an algorithm in the table.

coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex.name: coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex
coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the Authentication Algorithms Table.

coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithm.name: coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithm
coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithm.description: Identifies all the authentication algorithms supported by the STAs. The following are the default values and the their associated algorithms. Value = 1: Open System Value = 2: Shared Key

coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEnable.name: coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEnable
coDot11AuthenticationAlgorithmsEnable.description: This attribute, when true at a station, enables the acceptance of the authentication algorithm described in the corresponding table entry in authentication frames received by the station that have odd authentication sequence numbers. The default value of this attribute is 'true' for the Open System table entry and 'false' for all other table entries.

coDot11WEPDefaultKeysTable.name: coDot11WEPDefaultKeysTable
coDot11WEPDefaultKeysTable.description: Conceptual table for WEP default keys. This table contains the four WEP default secret key values corresponding to the four possible KeyID values. The WEP default secret keys are logically WRITE-ONLY. Attempts to read the entries in this table will return unsuccessful status and values of null or zero. The default value of each WEP default key is null. This table is not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11WEPDefaultKeysEntry.name: coDot11WEPDefaultKeysEntry
coDot11WEPDefaultKeysEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the WEP Default Keys Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex. coVirtualWlanProfileIndex - Uniquely access a profile for this particular 802.11 interface.

coDot11WEPDefaultKey1Value.name: coDot11WEPDefaultKey1Value
coDot11WEPDefaultKey1Value.description: A WEP default secret key1 value. Reading this attribute will always return a Zero-Length string.

coDot11WEPDefaultKey2Value.name: coDot11WEPDefaultKey2Value
coDot11WEPDefaultKey2Value.description: A WEP default secret key2 value. Reading this attribute will always return a Zero-Length string.

coDot11WEPDefaultKey3Value.name: coDot11WEPDefaultKey3Value
coDot11WEPDefaultKey3Value.description: A WEP default secret key3 value. Reading this attribute will always return a Zero-Length string.

coDot11WEPDefaultKey4Value.name: coDot11WEPDefaultKey4Value
coDot11WEPDefaultKey4Value.description: A WEP default secret key4 value. Reading this attribute will always return a Zero-Length string.

coDot11PrivacyTable.name: coDot11PrivacyTable
coDot11PrivacyTable.description: Group containing attributes related to IEEE 802.11 Privacy. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent. This table is not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11PrivacyEntry.name: coDot11PrivacyEntry
coDot11PrivacyEntry.description: An entry in the coDot11PrivacyTable Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex. coVirtualWlanProfileIndex - Uniquely access a profile for this particular 802.11 interface.

coDot11PrivacyInvoked.name: coDot11PrivacyInvoked
coDot11PrivacyInvoked.description: When this attribute is TRUE, it indicates that some level of security is invoked for transmitting frames of type Data. For IEEE 802.11-1999 clients, the security mechanism used is WEP. For RSNA-capable clients, an additional variable coDot11RSNAEnabled indicates whether RSNA is enabled. If coDot11RSNAEnabled is FALSE or the MIB variable does not exist, the security mechanism invoked is WEP; if coDot11RSNAEnabled is TRUE, RSNA security mechanisms invoked are configured in the coDot11RSNAConfigTable. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

coDot11WEPDefaultKeyID.name: coDot11WEPDefaultKeyID
coDot11WEPDefaultKeyID.description: This attribute indicates the use of the first, second, third, or fourth element of the WEPDefaultKeys array when set to values of zero, one, two, or three. The default value of this attribute is 0.

coDot11ExcludeUnencrypted.name: coDot11ExcludeUnencrypted
coDot11ExcludeUnencrypted.description: When this attribute is true, the STA does not indicate at the MAC service interface received MSDUs that have the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field equal to zero. When this attribute is false, the STA may accept MSDUs that have the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field equal to zero. The default value of this attribute shall be true.

coDot11WEPICVErrorCount.name: coDot11WEPICVErrorCount
coDot11WEPICVErrorCount.description: This counter increments when a frame is received with the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field set to one and the value of the ICV as received in the frame does not match the ICV value that is calculated for the contents of the received frame. ICV errors for TKIP are not counted in this variable but in coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPICVErrors.

coDot11WEPExcludedCount.name: coDot11WEPExcludedCount
coDot11WEPExcludedCount.description: This counter increments when a frame is received with the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field set to zero and the value of coDot11ExcludeUnencrypted causes that frame to be discarded.

coDot11RSNAEnabled.name: coDot11RSNAEnabled
coDot11RSNAEnabled.description: Indicates if RSNA is enabled, which means that the RSN Information Element is advertised in Beacons and Probe Responses. This object requires that coDot11PrivacyInvoked also be set to TRUE.

coDot11AssociationTable.name: coDot11AssociationTable
coDot11AssociationTable.description: Group containing attributes related to associated stations. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent. This table is not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11AssociationEntry.name: coDot11AssociationEntry
coDot11AssociationEntry.description: An entry in the coDot11Association Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex. coDot11AssociationIndex - Uniquely identify a device inside the association table.

coDot11AssociationIndex.name: coDot11AssociationIndex
coDot11AssociationIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the Association Table.

coDot11StationMACAddress.name: coDot11StationMACAddress
coDot11StationMACAddress.description: Unique MAC Address assigned to the device.

coDot11StationConnectTime.name: coDot11StationConnectTime
coDot11StationConnectTime.description: Elapsed time in seconds since a station has associated to this device.

coDot11SNR.name: coDot11SNR
coDot11SNR.description: Relative strength of the signal level compared to the noise level.

coDot11PktsRate1.name: coDot11PktsRate1
coDot11PktsRate1.description: Number of frames received at 1 Mbit/s.

coDot11PktsRate2.name: coDot11PktsRate2
coDot11PktsRate2.description: Number of frames received at 2 Mbit/s.

coDot11PktsRate5dot5.name: coDot11PktsRate5dot5
coDot11PktsRate5dot5.description: Number of frames received at 5.5 Mbit/s.

coDot11PktsRate11.name: coDot11PktsRate11
coDot11PktsRate11.description: Number of frames received at 11 Mbit/s.

coDot11PktsRate6.name: coDot11PktsRate6
coDot11PktsRate6.description: Number of frames received at 6 Mbit/s.

coDot11PktsRate9.name: coDot11PktsRate9
coDot11PktsRate9.description: Number of frames received at 9 Mbit/s.

coDot11PktsRate12.name: coDot11PktsRate12
coDot11PktsRate12.description: Number of frames received at 12 Mbit/s.

coDot11PktsRate18.name: coDot11PktsRate18
coDot11PktsRate18.description: Number of frames received at 18 Mbit/s.

coDot11PktsRate24.name: coDot11PktsRate24
coDot11PktsRate24.description: Number of frames received at 24 Mbit/s.

coDot11PktsRate36.name: coDot11PktsRate36
coDot11PktsRate36.description: Number of frames received at 36 Mbit/s.

coDot11PktsRate48.name: coDot11PktsRate48
coDot11PktsRate48.description: Number of frames received at 48 Mbit/s.

coDot11PktsRate54.name: coDot11PktsRate54
coDot11PktsRate54.description: Number of frames received at 54 Mbit/s.

coDot11TransmitRate.name: coDot11TransmitRate
coDot11TransmitRate.description: Current transmit rate of the associated station. This information is mostly used by the coDot11AssociationNotification event.

coDot11ReceiveRate.name: coDot11ReceiveRate
coDot11ReceiveRate.description: Current receive rate of the associated station.

coDot11InPkts.name: coDot11InPkts
coDot11InPkts.description: Number of packets received from the station after the association.

coDot11OutPkts.name: coDot11OutPkts
coDot11OutPkts.description: Number of packets send to the station after the association.

coDot11InOctets.name: coDot11InOctets
coDot11InOctets.description: Number of octets received from the station after the association.

coDot11OutOctets.name: coDot11OutOctets
coDot11OutOctets.description: Number of octets send to the station after the association.

coDot11StationIPAddress.name: coDot11StationIPAddress
coDot11StationIPAddress.description: IP address of the associated station.

coDot11StationVLAN.name: coDot11StationVLAN
coDot11StationVLAN.description: VLAN ID of the associated station. This object is always available on satellite devices. However, on access-controller devices, this object is only available under certain conditions, when the client station is connected to a profile that is not access-controlled.

coDot11StationLocalInterface.name: coDot11StationLocalInterface
coDot11StationLocalInterface.description: Specifies the Local Interface where the associated station traffic will be forwarded to.

coDot11WDSPortTable.name: coDot11WDSPortTable
coDot11WDSPortTable.description: Conceptual table for the WDS Ports. This table contains the six WDS MAC address. This table is not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11WDSPortEntry.name: coDot11WDSPortEntry
coDot11WDSPortEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the WDS Port Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex. coDot11WDSPortIndex - Uniquely identify a WDS port inside the WDS table.

coDot11WDSPortIndex.name: coDot11WDSPortIndex
coDot11WDSPortIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of WDS ports.

coDot11WDSPortMacAddress.name: coDot11WDSPortMacAddress
coDot11WDSPortMacAddress.description: MAC address of the remote device on the other side of the link.

coDot11WDSPortCurrentRate.name: coDot11WDSPortCurrentRate
coDot11WDSPortCurrentRate.description: Current rate of the WDS port.

coDot11WDSPortSNRLevel.name: coDot11WDSPortSNRLevel
coDot11WDSPortSNRLevel.description: Relative strength of the signal level compared to the noise level.

coDot11WDSPortTxPackets.name: coDot11WDSPortTxPackets
coDot11WDSPortTxPackets.description: Number of packets transmitted on this WDS port.

coDot11WDSPortTxDropped.name: coDot11WDSPortTxDropped
coDot11WDSPortTxDropped.description: Number of packets that could not be transmitted on this WDS port.

coDot11WDSPortTxErrors.name: coDot11WDSPortTxErrors
coDot11WDSPortTxErrors.description: Number of packets that could not be sent due to the following reasons: Rx retry limit exceeded or Tx discarded because of wrong SA.

coDot11WDSPortRxPackets.name: coDot11WDSPortRxPackets
coDot11WDSPortRxPackets.description: Number of packets received on this WDS port.

coDot11WDSPortRxDropped.name: coDot11WDSPortRxDropped
coDot11WDSPortRxDropped.description: Number of packets that were dropped on this WDS port due to a lack of resources.

coDot11WDSPortRxErrors.name: coDot11WDSPortRxErrors
coDot11WDSPortRxErrors.description: Number of packets that could not be received due to the following reasons: Rx discards WEP excluded, Rx discards WEP ICV error, Rx MSG in bad MSG fragments, Rx MSG in MSG fragments Rx WEP undecryptable, Rx FCS errors.

coDot11ScanTable.name: coDot11ScanTable
coDot11ScanTable.description: Conceptual table for the AP scanning results. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent. This table is not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11ScanEntry.name: coDot11ScanEntry
coDot11ScanEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the AP scan Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex. coDot11ScanIndex - Uniquely identify an AP in the scan Table.

coDot11ScanIndex.name: coDot11ScanIndex
coDot11ScanIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of AP in the scan table.

coDot11ScanMacAddress.name: coDot11ScanMacAddress
coDot11ScanMacAddress.description: The wireless MAC address of the remote device.

coDot11ScanChannel.name: coDot11ScanChannel
coDot11ScanChannel.description: The operating frequency channel of the remote device.

coDot11ScanSSID.name: coDot11ScanSSID
coDot11ScanSSID.description: The Service Set ID broadcast by the remote device.

coDot11ScanSNR.name: coDot11ScanSNR
coDot11ScanSNR.description: Relative strength of the signal level compared to the noise level.

coDot11ScanStatus.name: coDot11ScanStatus
coDot11ScanStatus.description: The status of the scanned device. 'unknown': The device could not determine the status of the scanned AP. 'authorized': The AP is part of the authorized list of APs. 'unauthorized': The AP is not part of the authorized list of APs.

coDot11ScanPHYType.name: coDot11ScanPHYType
coDot11ScanPHYType.description: Radio type used by the device.

coDot11ScanInactivityTime.name: coDot11ScanInactivityTime
coDot11ScanInactivityTime.description: Elapsed time since the last beacon was seen for this device.

coDot11ScanEnabled.name: coDot11ScanEnabled
coDot11ScanEnabled.description: Specifies if periodic scan should be performed or not. Not supported on the WCB-200. 'enable': Enables periodic scans on this device. 'disable': Disable periodic scans on this device.

coDot11ScanPeriodicity.name: coDot11ScanPeriodicity
coDot11ScanPeriodicity.description: Specifies the time between periodic scans. Each time a scan operation is performed, only one frequency is scanned. A fair amount of periodic scans are needed in order complete a full scan of all the supported frequencies. This parameter only applies when coDot11ScanEnabled is set to 'enable'. Not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11ScanAuthorizedListURL.name: coDot11ScanAuthorizedListURL
coDot11ScanAuthorizedListURL.description: Specifies the URL of the file that contains a list of all authorized access points. If no valid URL is present in this field, the AP will no be able to compute the rogue table. The format of this file is XML. Each entry in the file is composed of two items: MAC address and SSID. Each entry should appear on a new line. Not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11UnauthorizedAPNotificationEnabled.name: coDot11UnauthorizedAPNotificationEnabled
coDot11UnauthorizedAPNotificationEnabled.description: Specifies if periodic coDot11UnauthorizedAPNotification events are generated. Not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11UnauthorizedAPNotificationInterva.name: coDot11UnauthorizedAPNotificationInterval
coDot11UnauthorizedAPNotificationInterva.description: Interval in minutes between unauthorized AP notifications. Not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11AssociationNotificationEnabled.name: coDot11AssociationNotificationEnabled
coDot11AssociationNotificationEnabled.description: Specifies if coDot11AssociationNotification events are generated. Not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11AssociationNotificationInterval.name: coDot11AssociationNotificationInterval
coDot11AssociationNotificationInterval.description: Interval in minutes between association notifications. Setting this attribute to 0 will disable periodic sending of association notification. Not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11OperationTable.name: coDot11OperationTable
coDot11OperationTable.description: Group contains MAC attributes pertaining to the operation of the MAC. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent.

coDot11OperationEntry.name: coDot11OperationEntry
coDot11OperationEntry.description: An entry in the coDot11OperationEntry Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

coDot11MACAddress.name: coDot11MACAddress
coDot11MACAddress.description: Unique MAC Address assigned to the STA.

coDot11RTSThreshold.name: coDot11RTSThreshold
coDot11RTSThreshold.description: Indicated the number of octets in an MPDU, below which an RTS/CTS handshake is not performed. An RTS/CTS handshake is performed at the beginning of any frame exchange sequence where the MPDU is of type Data or Management, the MPDU has an individual address in the Address1 field, and the length of the MPDU is greater than this threshold. (For additional details, refer to Table 21 in 9.7.) Setting this attribute to be larger than the maximum MSDU size has the effect of turning off the RTS/CTS handshake for frames of Data or Management type transmitted by this STA. The default value of this attribute is 2347.

coDot11ShortRetryLimit.name: coDot11ShortRetryLimit
coDot11ShortRetryLimit.description: Indicates the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is less than or equal to coDot11RTSThreshold, that are made before a failure condition is indicated. The default value of this attribute is 7.

coDot11LongRetryLimit.name: coDot11LongRetryLimit
coDot11LongRetryLimit.description: Indicates the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is greater than coDot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated. The default value of this attribute is 4.

coDot11FragmentationThreshold.name: coDot11FragmentationThreshold
coDot11FragmentationThreshold.description: Indicates the current maximum size, in octets, of the MPDU that may be delivered to the PHY. An MSDU is broken down into fragments if its size exceeds the value of this attribute after adding MAC headers and trailers. An MSDU or MMPDU is fragmented when the resulting frame has an individual address in the Address1 field, and the length of the frame is larger than this threshold. The default value for this attribute is the lesser of 2346 or the aMPDUMaxLength of the attached PHY and will never exceed the lesser of 2346 or the aMPDUMaxLength of the attached PHY. The value of this attribute will never be less than 256.

coDot11MaxTransmitMSDULifetime.name: coDot11MaxTransmitMSDULifetime
coDot11MaxTransmitMSDULifetime.description: Elapsed time in TU after the initial transmission of an MSDU, after which further attempts to transmit the MSDU are terminated. The default value of this attribute is 512.

coDot11MaxReceiveLifetime.name: coDot11MaxReceiveLifetime
coDot11MaxReceiveLifetime.description: Elapsed time in TU, after the initial reception of a fragmented MMPDU or MSDU, after which further attempts to reassemble the MMPDU or MSDU is terminated. The default value is 512.

coDot11ManufacturerID.name: coDot11ManufacturerID
coDot11ManufacturerID.description: The name of the manufacturer. It may include additional information at the manufacturer's discretion. The default value of this attribute is null.

coDot11ProductID.name: coDot11ProductID
coDot11ProductID.description: An identifier that is unique to the manufacturer. It may include additional information at the manufacturer's discretion. The default value is null.

coDot11RadioType.name: coDot11RadioType
coDot11RadioType.description: Identify the wireless device inside the Alvarion product.

coDot11CountersTable.name: coDot11CountersTable
coDot11CountersTable.description: Group containing attributes that are MAC counters. In tabular form to allow multiple instance on an agent.

coDot11CountersEntry.name: coDot11CountersEntry
coDot11CountersEntry.description: An entry in the coDot11CountersEntry Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

coDot11TransmittedFragmentCount.name: coDot11TransmittedFragmentCount
coDot11TransmittedFragmentCount.description: This counter is incremented for an acknowledged MPDU with an individual address in the address 1 field or an MPDU with a multicast address in the address 1 field of type Data or Management.

coDot11MulticastTransmittedFrameCount.name: coDot11MulticastTransmittedFrameCount
coDot11MulticastTransmittedFrameCount.description: This counter is incremented only when the multicast bit is set in the destination MAC address of a successfully transmitted MSDU. When operating as a STA in an ESS, where these frames are directed to the AP, this implies having received an acknowledgment to all associated MPDUs.

coDot11FailedCount.name: coDot11FailedCount
coDot11FailedCount.description: This counter is incremented when an MSDU is not transmitted successfully due to the number of transmit attempts exceeding either the coDot11ShortRetryLimit or coDot11LongRetryLimit.

coDot11RetryCount.name: coDot11RetryCount
coDot11RetryCount.description: This counter is incremented when an MSDU is successfully transmitted after one or more retransmissions.

coDot11MultipleRetryCount.name: coDot11MultipleRetryCount
coDot11MultipleRetryCount.description: This counter is incremented when an MSDU is successfully transmitted after more than one retransmission.

coDot11FrameDuplicateCount.name: coDot11FrameDuplicateCount
coDot11FrameDuplicateCount.description: This counter is incremented when a frame is received that the Sequence Control field indicates is a duplicate.

coDot11RTSSuccessCount.name: coDot11RTSSuccessCount
coDot11RTSSuccessCount.description: This counter is incremented when a CTS is received in response to an RTS.

coDot11RTSFailureCount.name: coDot11RTSFailureCount
coDot11RTSFailureCount.description: This counter is incremented when a CTS is not received in response to an RTS.

coDot11ACKFailureCount.name: coDot11ACKFailureCount
coDot11ACKFailureCount.description: This counter is incremented when an ACK is not received when expected.

coDot11ReceivedFragmentCount.name: coDot11ReceivedFragmentCount
coDot11ReceivedFragmentCount.description: This counter is incremented for each successfully received MPDU of type Data or Management.

coDot11MulticastReceivedFrameCount.name: coDot11MulticastReceivedFrameCount
coDot11MulticastReceivedFrameCount.description: This counter is incremented when a MSDU is received with the multicast bit set in the destination MAC address.

coDot11FCSErrorCount.name: coDot11FCSErrorCount
coDot11FCSErrorCount.description: This counter is incremented when an FCS error is detected in a received MPDU.

coDot11TransmittedFrameCount.name: coDot11TransmittedFrameCount
coDot11TransmittedFrameCount.description: This counter is incremented for each successfully transmitted MSDU.

coDot11WEPUndecryptableCount.name: coDot11WEPUndecryptableCount
coDot11WEPUndecryptableCount.description: This counter is incremented when a frame is received with the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field set to one and the WEPOn value for the key mapped to the TA's MAC address indicates that the frame should not have been encrypted or that frame is discarded due to the receiving STA not implementing the privacy option.

coDot11PhyOperationTable.name: coDot11PhyOperationTable
coDot11PhyOperationTable.description: PHY level attributes concerned with operation. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent.

coDot11PhyOperationEntry.name: coDot11PhyOperationEntry
coDot11PhyOperationEntry.description: An entry in the coDot11PhyOperation Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

coDot11PHYType.name: coDot11PHYType
coDot11PHYType.description: This is an 8-bit integer value that identifies the PHY type supported by the attached PLCP and PMD. Currently defined values and their corresponding PHY types are: FHSS 2.4 GHz = 01 , DSSS 2.4 GHz = 02, IR Baseband = 03, OFDM 5 GHz = 04

coDot11CurrentRegDomain.name: coDot11CurrentRegDomain
coDot11CurrentRegDomain.description: The current regulatory domain this instance of the PMD is supporting. This object corresponds to one of the RegDomains listed in coDot11RegDomainsSupported.

coDot11TempType.name: coDot11TempType
coDot11TempType.description: There are different operating temperature requirements dependent on the anticipated environmental conditions. This attribute describes the current PHY's operating temperature range capability. Currently defined values and their corresponding temperature ranges are: Type 1 = X'01'-Commercial range of 0 to 40 degrees C, Type 2 = X'02'-Industrial range of -30 to 70 degrees C.

coDot11CurrentOperFrequency.name: coDot11CurrentOperFrequency
coDot11CurrentOperFrequency.description: The current operating frequency channel of the radio.

coDot11CurrentOperPHYType.name: coDot11CurrentOperPHYType
coDot11CurrentOperPHYType.description: The current operating phy type of the radio.

coDot11RadioEnabled.name: coDot11RadioEnabled
coDot11RadioEnabled.description: When True the radio is enabled.

coDot11OperatingMode.name: coDot11OperatingMode
coDot11OperatingMode.description: Operating mode of the radio. Available options are: Access point and Wireless links: Standard operating mode provides support for all wireless functions. Access point only: Only provides access point functionality, wireless links cannot be created. Wireless links only: Only provides wireless links functionality. Wireless client stations cannot connect. Monitor: Enables the radio to be used for monitoring (wireless neighborhood) only. Both access point and wireless links functionality are disabled.

coDot11AutoChannelEnabled.name: coDot11AutoChannelEnabled
coDot11AutoChannelEnabled.description: When True the Auto Channel option is enabled.

coDot11AutoChannelInterval.name: coDot11AutoChannelInterval
coDot11AutoChannelInterval.description: Time interval, in minutes, between auto rescanning of the channels. Maximum is 1440 minutes (24 hours). A value of zero disables automatic rescanning of channels, the radio will automatically select a channel when the interface intializes and utilize that channel as long as the interface is operational.

coDot11AutoPowerEnabled.name: coDot11AutoPowerEnabled
coDot11AutoPowerEnabled.description: When True the Auto Power option is enabled.

coDot11AutoPowerInterval.name: coDot11AutoPowerInterval
coDot11AutoPowerInterval.description: Time interval, in minutes, between auto rescanning of the channels. Maximum is 1440 minutes (24 hours).

coDot11PhyAntennaTable.name: coDot11PhyAntennaTable
coDot11PhyAntennaTable.description: Group of attributes for PhyAntenna. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent.

coDot11PhyAntennaEntry.name: coDot11PhyAntennaEntry
coDot11PhyAntennaEntry.description: An entry in the coDot11PhyAntenna Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

coDot11CurrentTxAntenna.name: coDot11CurrentTxAntenna
coDot11CurrentTxAntenna.description: The current antenna being used to transmit. This value is one of the values appearing in coDot11SupportedTxAntenna. This may be used by a management agent to control which antenna is used for transmission.

coDot11DiversitySupport.name: coDot11DiversitySupport
coDot11DiversitySupport.description: This implementation's support for diversity, encoded as: X'01': Diversity is available and is performed over the fixed list of antennas defined in coDot11DiversitySelectionRx. X'02': Diversity is not supported. X'03': Diversity is supported and control of diversity is also available, in which case the attribute coDot11DiversitySelectionRx can be dynamically modified by the LME.

coDot11CurrentRxAntenna.name: coDot11CurrentRxAntenna
coDot11CurrentRxAntenna.description: The current antenna being used to receive, if the coDot11 DiversitySupport indicates that diversity is not supported. The selected antenna shall be one of the antennae marked for receive in the coDot11AntennasListTable.

coDot11PhyConfigTable.name: coDot11PhyConfigTable
coDot11PhyConfigTable.description: PHY configuration attributes. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent.

coDot11PhyConfigEntry.name: coDot11PhyConfigEntry
coDot11PhyConfigEntry.description: An entry in the coDot11PhyConfig Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

coDot11PhyAdminStatus.name: coDot11PhyAdminStatus
coDot11PhyAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the radio interface. 'up': Sets the radio interface to be ready to pass packets. 'down': Stops the transmit and receive of packets on the interface.

coDot11PhyOperStatus.name: coDot11PhyOperStatus
coDot11PhyOperStatus.description: The current state of the radio interface. 'up': The radio interface is ready to pass packets. 'down': The radio is not able to transmit nor receive packets on the interface.

coDot11PhyDSSSTable.name: coDot11PhyDSSSTable
coDot11PhyDSSSTable.description: Entry of attributes for coDot11PhyDSSSEntry. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent. This table only apply when in DSSS 2.4 GHz range

coDot11PhyDSSSEntry.name: coDot11PhyDSSSEntry
coDot11PhyDSSSEntry.description: An entry in the coDot11PhyDSSSEntry Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

coDot11CurrentChannel.name: coDot11CurrentChannel
coDot11CurrentChannel.description: The desired operating frequency channel of the DSSS PHY. Valid channel numbers are as defined in 15.4.6.2.

coDot11CCAModeSupported.name: coDot11CCAModeSupported
coDot11CCAModeSupported.description: coDot11CCAModeSupported is a bit-significant value, representing all of the CCA modes supported by the PHY. Valid values are: energy detect only (ED_ONLY) = 01, carrier sense only (CS_ONLY) = 02, carrier sense and energy detect (ED_and_CS)= 04 or the logical sum of any of these values.

coDot11CurrentCCAMode.name: coDot11CurrentCCAMode
coDot11CurrentCCAMode.description: The current CCA method in operation. Valid values are: energy detect only (edonly) = 01, carrier sense only (csonly) = 02, carrier sense and energy detect (edandcs)= 04.

coDot11RegDomainsSupportedTable.name: coDot11RegDomainsSupportedTable
coDot11RegDomainsSupportedTable.description: There are different operational requirements dependent on the regulatory domain. This attribute list describes the regulatory domains the PLCP and PMD support in this implementation. Currently defined values and their corresponding Regulatory Domains are: FCC (USA) = X'10', DOC (Canada) = X'20', ETSI (most of Europe) = X'30', Spain = X'31', France = X'32', Japan = X'41'

coDot11RegDomainsSupportedEntry.name: coDot11RegDomainsSupportedEntry
coDot11RegDomainsSupportedEntry.description: An entry in the coDot11RegDomainsSupported Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex. coDot11RegDomainsSupportIndex - Uniquely specifies the regulatory domain in the table.

coDot11RegDomainsSupportIndex.name: coDot11RegDomainsSupportIndex
coDot11RegDomainsSupportIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the RegDomainsSupported Table.

coDot11RegDomainsSupportValue.name: coDot11RegDomainsSupportValue
coDot11RegDomainsSupportValue.description: There are different operational requirements dependent on the regulatory domain. This attribute list describes the regulatory domains the PLCP and PMD support in this implementation. Currently defined values and their corresponding Regulatory Domains are: FCC (USA) = X'10', DOC (Canada) = X'20', ETSI (most of Europe) = X'30', Spain = X'31', France = X'32', Japan = X'41'

coDot11AntennasListTable.name: coDot11AntennasListTable
coDot11AntennasListTable.description: This table represents the list of antennae. An antenna can be marked to be capable of transmitting, receiving, and/or for participation in receive diversity. Each entry in this table represents a single antenna with its properties. The maximum number of antennae that can be contained in this table is 255.

coDot11AntennasListEntry.name: coDot11AntennasListEntry
coDot11AntennasListEntry.description: An entry in the coDot11AntennasListTable, representing the properties of a single antenna. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex. coDot11AntennaListIndex - Uniquely identifies the antenna connected to the 802.11 interface.

coDot11AntennaListIndex.name: coDot11AntennaListIndex
coDot11AntennaListIndex.description: The unique index of an antenna which is used to identify the columnar objects in the coDot11AntennasList Table.

coDot11SupportedTxAntenna.name: coDot11SupportedTxAntenna
coDot11SupportedTxAntenna.description: When true, this object indicates that the antenna represented by coDot11AntennaIndex can be used as a transmit antenna.

coDot11SupportedRxAntenna.name: coDot11SupportedRxAntenna
coDot11SupportedRxAntenna.description: When true, this object indicates that the antenna represented by the coDot11AntennaIndex can be used as a receive antenna.

coDot11DiversitySelectionRx.name: coDot11DiversitySelectionRx
coDot11DiversitySelectionRx.description: When true, this object indicates that the antenna represented by coDot11AntennaIndex can be used for receive diversity. This object may only be true if the antenna can be used as a receive antenna, as indicated by coDot11SupportedRxAntenna.

coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxTable.name: coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxTable
coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxTable.description: The Transmit bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, data rates are increments of 500Kb/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s subject to limitations of each individual PHY.

coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxEntry.name: coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxEntry
coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the coDot11SupportedDataRatesTx Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex. coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxIndex - Uniquely identifies a supported rate in the table.

coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxIndex.name: coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxIndex
coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxIndex.description: Index object which identifies which data rate to access.

coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxValue.name: coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxValue
coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxValue.description: The Transmit bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, data rates are increments of 500Kb/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s subject to limitations of each individual PHY.

coDot11SupportedDataRatesRxTable.name: coDot11SupportedDataRatesRxTable
coDot11SupportedDataRatesRxTable.description: The receive bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, data rates are increments of 500Kb/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s subject to limitations of each individual PHY.

coDot11SupportedDataRatesRxEntry.name: coDot11SupportedDataRatesRxEntry
coDot11SupportedDataRatesRxEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the coDot11SupportedDataRatesRx Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex. coDot11SupportedDataRatesTxIndex - Uniquely identifies a supported rate in the table.

coDot11SupportedDataRatesRxIndex.name: coDot11SupportedDataRatesRxIndex
coDot11SupportedDataRatesRxIndex.description: Index object which identifies which data rate to access.

coDot11SupportedDataRatesRxValue.name: coDot11SupportedDataRatesRxValue
coDot11SupportedDataRatesRxValue.description: The receive bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, data rates are increments of 500Kb/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s subject to limitations of each individual PHY.

coDot11PhyOFDMTable.name: coDot11PhyOFDMTable
coDot11PhyOFDMTable.description: Entry of attributes for coDot11PhyOFDMEntry. In tabular form to allow multiple instances on an agent. This table only apply when in OFDM 5 GHz range.

coDot11PhyOFDMEntry.name: coDot11PhyOFDMEntry
coDot11PhyOFDMEntry.description: An entry in the coDot11PhyOFDMEntry Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

coDot11CurrentFrequency.name: coDot11CurrentFrequency
coDot11CurrentFrequency.description: The desired operating frequency channel of the OFDM PHY.

coDot11TIThreshold.name: coDot11TIThreshold
coDot11TIThreshold.description: The threshold being used to detect a busy medium (frequency). CCA shall report a busy medium upon detecting the RSSI above this threshold.

coDot11FrequencyBandsSupported.name: coDot11FrequencyBandsSupported
coDot11FrequencyBandsSupported.description: The capability of the OFDM PHY implementation to operate in the three U-NII bands. Coded as an integer value of a three bit fields as follow: bit 0 .. capable of operating in the lower (5.15-5.25 GHz) U-NII band. bit 1 .. capable of operating in the middle (5.25-5.35 GHz) U-NII band. bit 2 .. capable of operating in the middle (5.725-5.825 GHz) U-NII band. For example, for an implementation capable of operating in the lower and middle bands, this attribute would take the value 3.

coDot11MinimumSNRLevel.name: coDot11MinimumSNRLevel
coDot11MinimumSNRLevel.description: An SNR level notification is generated when the average SNR level is below this attribute. Not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11SNRLevelNotificationEnabled.name: coDot11SNRLevelNotificationEnabled
coDot11SNRLevelNotificationEnabled.description: This attribute, when true, enables the generation of SNR level notifications. Not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11SNRLevelNotificationInterval.name: coDot11SNRLevelNotificationInterval
coDot11SNRLevelNotificationInterval.description: Interval in minutes between SNR Level notifications. Not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11CountryCode.name: coDot11CountryCode
coDot11CountryCode.description: The radios are running accordingly to the regulations of this country.

coDot11RSNAStatsTable.name: coDot11RSNAStatsTable
coDot11RSNAStatsTable.description: This table maintains statistics for SN. It is not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11RSNAStatsVersion.name: coDot11RSNAStatsVersion
coDot11RSNAStatsVersion.description: The RSNA version which the AP associated with.

coDot11RSNAStatsSelectedPairwiseCipher.name: coDot11RSNAStatsSelectedPairwiseCipher
coDot11RSNAStatsSelectedPairwiseCipher.description: The AKM Suite the AP selected during association. The value consists of a three octet OUI followed by a one octet type as follows: OUI Value, Cipher, Type XX-XX-XX, 0, Reserved XX-XX-XX, 1, WEP-40 XX-XX-XX, 2, TKIP XX-XX-XX, 3, Reserved XX-XX-XX, 4, CCMP XX-XX-XX, 5, WEP-104 XX-XX-XX, 6-255, Reserved Vendor, any, Vendor Specific other, any, Reserved

coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPICVErrors.name: coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPICVErrors
coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPICVErrors.description: Counts the number of TKIP ICV errors encountered when decrypting packets for the AP.

coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPLocalMICFailures.name: coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPLocalMICFailures
coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPLocalMICFailures.description: Counts the number of Michael MIC failure encountered when checking the integrity of packets received from the AP at this entity.

coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPRemoteMICFailures.name: coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPRemoteMICFailures
coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPRemoteMICFailures.description: Counts the number of Michael MIC failures encountered by the remote device and reported back to this entity.

coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPCounterMeasuresInvok.name: coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPCounterMeasuresInvoked
coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPCounterMeasuresInvok.description: Counts the number of times a MIC failure occurred two times within 60 seconds and countermeasures were invoked. This variable counts this for both local and remote. It increments every time countermeasures are invoked.

coDot11RSNAStatsCCMPFormatErrors.name: coDot11RSNAStatsCCMPFormatErrors
coDot11RSNAStatsCCMPFormatErrors.description: The number of MSDUs received with an invalid CCMP format.

coDot11RSNAStatsCCMPReplays.name: coDot11RSNAStatsCCMPReplays
coDot11RSNAStatsCCMPReplays.description: The number of received unicast fragments discarded by the replay mechanism.

coDot11RSNAStatsCCMPDecryptErrors.name: coDot11RSNAStatsCCMPDecryptErrors
coDot11RSNAStatsCCMPDecryptErrors.description: The number of received fragments discarded by the CCMP decryption algorithm.

coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPReplays.name: coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPReplays
coDot11RSNAStatsTKIPReplays.description: Counts the number of TKIP replay errors detected.

coDot11RSNAStats4WayHandshakeFailures.name: coDot11RSNAStats4WayHandshakeFailures
coDot11RSNAStats4WayHandshakeFailures.description: Counts the number of 4-Way Handshake failures.

coDot11SNRLevelNotification.name: coDot11SNRLevelNotification
coDot11SNRLevelNotification.description: The average SNR level for all the stations using this virtual ap during the last three intervals is low.

coDot11AssociationNotification.name: coDot11AssociationNotification
coDot11AssociationNotification.description: Sent when a new association is made or sent periodically using interval specified by coDot11AssociationNotificationInterval object.

coDot11UnauthorizedAPNotification.name: coDot11UnauthorizedAPNotification
coDot11UnauthorizedAPNotification.description: Sent when a new unauthorized AP is detected.

coDot11Compliance.name: coDot11Compliance
coDot11Compliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities that implement the IEEE 802.11 MIB.

coDot11RSNCompliance.name: coDot11RSNCompliance
coDot11RSNCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities that implement the IEEE 802.11 RSN MIB.

coDot11APBaseGroup.name: coDot11APBaseGroup
coDot11APBaseGroup.description: The AP object class provides the necessary support at the Access Point to manage the processes in the STA such that the STA may work cooperatively as a part of an IEEE 802.11 network.

coDot11APPrivacyGroup.name: coDot11APPrivacyGroup
coDot11APPrivacyGroup.description: The APPrivacy package is a set of attributes that shall be present if WEP is implemented in the Access Point.

coDot11MACBaseGroup.name: coDot11MACBaseGroup
coDot11MACBaseGroup.description: The MAC object class provides the necessary support for the access control, generation, and verification of frame check sequences, and proper delivery of valid data to upper layers.

coDot11MACStatisticsGroup.name: coDot11MACStatisticsGroup
coDot11MACStatisticsGroup.description: The MACStatistics package provides extended statistical information on the operation of the MAC. This package is completely optional.

coDot11PhyDSSSComplianceGroup.name: coDot11PhyDSSSComplianceGroup
coDot11PhyDSSSComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the DSSS for IEEE 802.11.

coDot11PhyRegDomainsSupportGroup.name: coDot11PhyRegDomainsSupportGroup
coDot11PhyRegDomainsSupportGroup.description: Attributes that specify the supported Regulation Domains.

coDot11PhyRateGroup.name: coDot11PhyRateGroup
coDot11PhyRateGroup.description: Attributes for Data Rates for IEEE 802.11.

coDot11CountersGroup.name: coDot11CountersGroup
coDot11CountersGroup.description: Attributes from the coDot11CountersGroup that are not described in the coDot11MACStatistics group. These objects are mandatory.

coDot11AssociationGroup.name: coDot11AssociationGroup
coDot11AssociationGroup.description: The AP object class provides the necessary support at the Access Point to manage the association table.

coDot11AssociationConfigGroup.name: coDot11AssociationConfigGroup
coDot11AssociationConfigGroup.description: The AP object class provides the necessary support at the Access Point to manage the association table. Not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11ScanGroup.name: coDot11ScanGroup
coDot11ScanGroup.description: The AP object class provides the necessary support at the Access Point to manage the scan table.

coDot11ScanConfigGroup.name: coDot11ScanConfigGroup
coDot11ScanConfigGroup.description: The AP object class provides the necessary support at the Access Point to manage the scan table. Not supported on the WCB-200.

coDot11WDSComplianceGroup.name: coDot11WDSComplianceGroup
coDot11WDSComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the WDS table.

coDot11RSNBase.name: coDot11RSNBase
coDot11RSNBase.description: The coDot11RSNBase object class provides the necessary support for managing RSNA functionality in the STA

coDot11PhyOFDMComplianceGroup.name: coDot11PhyOFDMComplianceGroup
coDot11PhyOFDMComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the OFDM for IEEE 802.11.
